	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm not aware of disciplines that make tanks invulnerable...exactly.&nbsp;&nbsp;I know of Riposte disciplines, where for the duration of the discipline the tank ripostes EVERY attack.  =)  I think, but can't be sure, that there is something similar to this, but with Dodge instead.  I'm not sure if the mobs' AI would cause them to react to this as invulnerability precisely...If they did, that would wind up making these disciplines practically worthless now.  What I think the change was supposed to do was more along the lines of...say...for example the Enchanter Rune spells.  If a mob takes a swing at someone and sees "Soandso's magical skin absorbs the damage," they may be more likely to find another target in your group, of if the Cleric casts Divine Aura, the mob may go to whoever is next on his hate list, and leave the Cleric alone while the Tanks hopefully accumulate enough taunt before DA wears off.  <br>I think the change was meant for spells like this...if it has the same effect for Disciplines like what I've heard of...well, I guess we won't see any of THOSE being used anymore in groups...  =\<br>But, like I said I'm not sure.  It's the kind of thing we'll learn more about as time passes.<br><br>Jarochai Alabaster<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
